cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on generating sentence-level distractors for reading comprehension, which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a neural-based method using a sequence-to-sequence model, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The model also involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses semantic similarity, which is a topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
